AFRICAN National Congress (ANC) veteran Billy Modise has died at the age of 88. Modise passed away on Wednesday night after being in hospital for a while. The former High Commissioner to Canada Ambassador was at the Unitas Hospital in Pretoria. He was also the chief of state security under the Thabo Mbeki administration until he retired in 2006. Modise was born on 8 December 1930 in Bloemfontein in the then-Orange Free State. In 1975, Modise worked in New York did work for Habitat, at the United Nations (UN) Conference on Human Settlements. He also worked as Assistant Director of the United Nations Institute for Namibia in Lusaka, Zambia where he closely worked with Namibians, providing training in political science, sociology and on education.  